article.description: Seneca Knight had 20 points as San Jose State defeated Air Force 90-81 on Saturday.
article.headline: Knight scores 20 to carry San Jose St. past Air Force 90-81
article.linkText: Knight scores 20 to carry San Jose St. past Air Force 90-81
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Seneca Knight had 20 points as San Jose State defeated Air Force 90-81 on Saturday. Brae Ivey had 17 points for San Jose State (7-14, 3-6 Mountain West Conference). Richard Washington added 12 points. Eduardo Lane had 11 points. Omari Moore had 9 points and 10 assists. The 90 points were a season best for San Jose State. Lavelle Scottie had 25 points and five assists for the Falcons (9-12, 3-6). Caleb Morris added 13 points and six assists. Chris Joyce had 12 points. San Jose State plays Boise State on the road on Wednesday. Air Force plays Fresno State at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
